From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Electron Scripts <scripts@electron>
Date: Wed, 22 Apr 2026 14:11:03 +0200
Subject: zlib: normalize brotli decoder error codes for Chromium's brotli

Chromium's brotli fork returns just the NAME portion from
BrotliDecoderErrorString() (e.g. "FORMAT_RESERVED") whereas Node.js'
bundled brotli returns "_ERROR_FORMAT_..." style strings. The JS
layer's handleKnownInternalErrors() (adapters.js) classifies brotli
failures as TypeError by matching the "ERR__ERROR_" prefix, which
only works against the bundled behavior. Normalize the emitted code
so the Compression Streams spec-compliant TypeError is produced
regardless of which brotli implementation Node is linked against.

This patch can be removed when Chromium's brotli returns the full
"_ERROR_..." prefix matching upstream brotli, or when Node removes
the string-prefix-based classification in favor of a numeric or
well-known error code.

diff --git a/src/node_zlib.cc b/src/node_zlib.cc
index 792d800847e10528fc383e0d797b098aaa96b8d4..ce2d41ef8114fc4f83b4c9b109cd93426a2a0e3d 100644
--- a/src/node_zlib.cc
+++ b/src/node_zlib.cc
@@ -1512,7 +1512,15 @@ void BrotliDecoderContext::DoThreadPoolWork() {
   next_in_ += next_in - next_in_;
   if (last_result_ == BROTLI_DECODER_RESULT_ERROR) {
     error_ = BrotliDecoderGetErrorCode(state_.get());
-    error_string_ = std::string("ERR_") + BrotliDecoderErrorString(error_);
+    const char* brotli_err = BrotliDecoderErrorString(error_);
+    // Node.js' bundled brotli's BrotliDecoderErrorString() returns codes
+    // like "_ERROR_FORMAT_...", but Chromium's brotli (used in Electron)
+    // returns only the trailing NAME (e.g. "FORMAT_..."). Normalize to the
+    // "ERR__ERROR_..." prefix the adapters layer relies on to classify
+    // brotli failures as TypeError.
+    error_string_ = (brotli_err[0] == '_' ? std::string("ERR_")
+                                          : std::string("ERR__ERROR_")) +
+                    brotli_err;
   }
 }
 
